  <p class="cont">forbid any man leaving just as we are going to close the meeting. He is no gentleman who will do
  it. I don&rsquo;t care who does it, even if it were the king of England. I forbid it. (April 16, 1843.) DHC
  5:360–363.</p>
  <div class="topic">Salvation Through Knowledge</div>
  <p class="std">It is not wisdom that we should have all knowledge at once presented before us;<span class="footRef">1</span> but that we
  should have a little at a time;<span class="footRef">2</span> then we can comprehend it. President Smith then read the 2nd Epistle
  of Peter, 1st chapter, 16th to last verses,<span class="footRef">3</span> and dwelt upon the 19th verse<span class="footRef">4</span> with some remarks.</p>
  <p class="std">Add to your faith knowledge,<span class="footRef">5</span> etc. The principle of knowledge is the principle of salvation.<span class="footRef">6</span>
  This principle can be comprehended by the faithful and diligent;<span class="footRef">7</span> and every one that does not obtain
  knowledge sufficient to be saved will be condemned.<span class="footRef">8</span> The principle of salvation is given us through
  the knowledge<span class="footRef">9</span> of Jesus Christ.<span class="footRef">10</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Salvation Is to Triumph over Enemies</div>
  <p class="std">Salvation<span class="footRef">11</span> is nothing more nor less than to triumph over all<span class="footRef">12</span> our enemies<span class="footRef">13</span> and put them under
  our feet. And when we have power to put all enemies under our feet<span class="footRef">14</span> in this world, and a knowledge
  to triumph over all evil spirits<span class="footRef">15</span> in the world to come, then we are saved, as in the case of Jesus, who
  was to reign until He had put all enemies under His feet,<span class="footRef">16</span> and the last enemy was death.<span class="footRef">17</span></p>
  <div class="topic">No Salvation Without a Tabernacle</div>
  <p class="std">Perhaps there are principles here that few men have thought of. No person can have this
  salvation except through a tabernacle.</p>
  <p class="std">Now, in this world, mankind are naturally selfish,<span class="footRef">18</span> ambitious<span class="footRef">19</span> and striving to excel one above
  another;<span class="footRef">20</span> yet some are willing to build up others as well as themselves.<span class="footRef">21</span> So in the other world there
  are a variety of spirits. Some seek to excel.<span class="footRef">22</span> And this was the case with Lucifer when he fell.<span class="footRef">23</span> He
  sought for things which were unlawful.<span class="footRef">24</span> Hence he was sent down,<span class="footRef">25</span> and it is said he drew many
  away with him;<span class="footRef">26</span> and the greatness of his punishment is that he shall not have a tabernacle.<span class="footRef">27</span> This
  is his punishment. So the devil, thinking to thwart the decree of God,<span class="footRef">28</span> by going up and down in the
  earth,<span class="footRef">29</span> seeking whom he</p>
